translated: Dahlgren, Erik Gustaf was a provincial doctor from Mönsterås. He was born on February 23, 1892 in Stockholm to E.W. Dahlgren and Leon-tine Cabré. He was married twice, first to Margareta Lidberg in 1926, who passed away in 1928, and then to Elsa Fritzén in 1932. He had four children: Carl-Erik born in 1927, Lars Erik born in 1933 but passed away in 1935, Sven Erik Vilhelm born in 1934, and Bengt Erik born in 1938. He graduated from secondary school in 1912, received a Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1918, and a medical license in 1926, all from Stockholm. He worked as a medical doctor at Saltsjöbadens bathhouse and Romanäs sanatorium in 1925, as temporary second assistant doctor at Eskilstuna hospital in 1926, and at Sundsvall hospital medical ward from 1926-1927, later as temporary second assistant doctor from 1927-1928. He was also a temporary assistant doctor at Allmänna BB in Stockholm in 1928, temporary second assistant doctor at Sundsvall hospital medical ward, as well as temporary provincial doctor in Alnö and Fellingsbro district in 1929, and in Varberg district in 1930. From 1930-1931, he served as provincial doctor and district doctor in Alingsås, Mora, Bredbyn, and Rimbö districts, then as provisional and dispensary doctor in Junsele district in 1931, and finally as provincial doctor in Mönsterås district from 1939 onwards. He was a member of the health council in Mönsterås and the temperance union there.
